<subSubSection id="CAAE6535FFE0FF8BFF7BFD39FEB4FCDE" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFE0FF8BFF7BFD39FEB4FCDE" blockId="92.[189,1399,741,869]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
This large, predominantly Italian genus was reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFE0FF8BFCB9FD39FB80FD44" author="Spelda J." box="[895,1069,741,767]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="5 - 48" refId="ref39559" refString="Spelda J. 2008. The genus Pyrgocyphosoma Verhoeff, 1910 (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida: Craspedosomatidae): New aspects on systematics, distribution and ecology. Schubartiana 3: 5 - 48." type="journal article" year="2008">Spelda (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. It is not clear in all cases whether a taxon is to be regarded as a species or a subspecies. All taxa with a separate entry in 
<bibRefCitation id="E6254B4FFFE0FF8BFAE1FCDBFEA1FCF8" author="Spelda J." pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="5 - 48" refId="ref39559" refString="Spelda J. 2008. The genus Pyrgocyphosoma Verhoeff, 1910 (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida: Craspedosomatidae): New aspects on systematics, distribution and ecology. Schubartiana 3: 5 - 48." type="journal article" year="2008">Spelda (2008)</bibRefCitation>
are here listed as species although some may turn out to be subspecies or synonyms of other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
